# KGHub Production Server

## Credentials

All secrets live in `.env.server` at the project root (git-ignored). Read it before running any server commands:

```bash
source .env.server
# Variables: SERVER_IP, SERVER_SSH_PORT, DEPLOY_USER, DEPLOY_PASSWORD,
#            DB_NAME, DB_USER, DB_PASSWORD
```

## Connection

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| IP | `$SERVER_IP` (see `.env.server`) |
| SSH Port | `2222` |
| Deploy user | `kghubdeploy` (password in `.env.server`) |
| App user | `kghubapp` (owns `/opt/kghub/app`, runs PM2) |
| cPanel user | `kghubweb` (owns `kghub.ai` vhosts) |
| Platform root | `/opt/kghub/app` |
| OS | AlmaLinux 9 тАФ use `dnf`, never `apt` |

```bash
source .env.server
ssh -p $SERVER_SSH_PORT $DEPLOY_USER@$SERVER_IP
```

## Architecture

- **Web layer**: Apache managed by cPanel/WHM тАФ do NOT install standalone Nginx
- **SSL**: cPanel AutoSSL (Let's Encrypt) тАФ certs live on Apache vhosts
- **App**: Next.js 16 on port 4000, managed by PM2 as `kghubapp`
- **Database**: PostgreSQL 17, localhost only тАФ DB `kghub_prod`, user `kghub_db_user` (password in `.env.server` тЖТ `DB_PASSWORD`)
- **Storage**: DigitalOcean Spaces (`kghub` bucket, `tor1` region)
- **Domains**: `admin.kghub.ai` тЖТ frontend, `api.kghub.ai` тЖТ API (same Next.js process)

## Apache Reverse Proxy

Include files (survive `rebuildhttpdconf`) live at:
- HTTP:  `/etc/apache2/conf.d/userdata/std/2_4/kghubweb/<domain>/proxy.conf`
- HTTPS: `/etc/apache2/conf.d/userdata/ssl/2_4/kghubweb/<domain>/proxy.conf`

After editing any include file, always run:
```bash
sudo /scripts/rebuildhttpdconf
sudo /usr/local/cpanel/scripts/restartsrv_httpd
```

## PM2

```bash
# Check status
sudo -u kghubapp bash -c "export HOME=/home/kghubapp; /usr/local/lib/node_modules/pm2/bin/pm2 list"

# Restart app
sudo -u kghubapp /usr/local/lib/node_modules/pm2/bin/pm2 restart kghub

# Logs
sudo -u kghubapp /usr/local/lib/node_modules/pm2/bin/pm2 logs kghub --lines 50 --nostream
```

## Manual Deploy (without CI/CD)

```bash
cd /opt/kghub/app
sudo -u kghubapp git pull origin main
sudo -u kghubapp npm ci --omit=dev
sudo -u kghubapp /opt/kghub/app/node_modules/.bin/prisma generate
sudo -u kghubapp npm run build
sudo -u kghubapp /opt/kghub/app/node_modules/.bin/prisma migrate deploy
sudo -u kghubapp /usr/local/lib/node_modules/pm2/bin/pm2 restart kghub
```

## CI/CD (GitHub Actions)

- Workflow: `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` тАФ triggers on push to `main`
- Secret required: `SSH_PRIVATE_KEY` тЖТ private half of `/tmp/kghub_cicd_key` (generated during deploy session)
- Public key already installed on server at `/home/kghubdeploy/.ssh/authorized_keys`
- Sudoers rule at `/etc/sudoers.d/kghubdeploy-deploy` allows `kghubdeploy` to run deploy commands as `kghubapp`

## kghub.ai Landing Page

- File: `/home/kghubweb/public_html/index.html` (self-contained, logos base64-embedded)
- To update: edit `public/index.html` locally then:
```bash
source .env.server
sshpass -p "$DEPLOY_PASSWORD" scp -P $SERVER_SSH_PORT public/index.html $DEPLOY_USER@$SERVER_IP:/tmp/kghub_index.html
sshpass -p "$DEPLOY_PASSWORD" ssh -p $SERVER_SSH_PORT $DEPLOY_USER@$SERVER_IP \
  'sudo cp /tmp/kghub_index.html /home/kghubweb/public_html/index.html && sudo chown kghubweb:kghubweb /home/kghubweb/public_html/index.html'
```

## Key npm Notes

- `prisma` and `@prisma/client` are in `dependencies` (not devDependencies) тАФ required at build time
- `@tailwindcss/postcss`, `tailwindcss`, `postcss`, `autoprefixer` are in `dependencies` тАФ required at build time
- `.npmrc` has `legacy-peer-deps=true` to resolve `@auth/core` peer dep conflict
- Build command: `npm ci --omit=dev && prisma generate && npm run build`
